# Progress System

The Progress System is the intelligence layer of learning measurement.

It answers: "How well is the user learning?"

---

# Product Vision

Progress must:

- track learning effectiveness
- identify weak areas
- show mastery levels
- motivate consistent learning
- guide AI recommendations

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

ProgressController (Riverpod)

↓

ProgressState

↓

ProgressRepository

↓

Analytics Engine

---

# State Management

ProgressState includes:

- loading
- updated
- syncing
- error

Core Data:

- courseProgress
- lessonProgress
- quizPerformance
- examScores
- streakData
- masteryMap

---

# Mastery Model

Each topic has:

- beginner
- intermediate
- advanced
- mastered

Based on:

- quiz performance
- revision frequency
- exam results

---

# Weak Area Detection

AI identifies weak areas based on:

- repeated mistakes
- low accuracy topics
- slow response time
- inconsistent performance

---

# Streak System

Tracks:

- daily study streak
- weekly consistency
- longest streak

Must include:

- streak freeze logic (future)
- reset protection rules

---

# Analytics Aggregation

Progress aggregates data from:

- Courses
- Quizzes
- Exams
- Flashcards
- Lesson interactions

---

# Offline Behaviour

- local progress tracking
- sync when online
- merge conflict resolution required

---

# API Contracts

GET /progress

GET /progress/courses

GET /progress/mastery

POST /progress/update

---

# Analytics Events

progress_view

progress_update

progress_milestone_reached

streak_updated

mastery_level_up

---

# UI Composition Rules

Progress UI must include:

- mastery heatmap
- streak tracker
- weak topics list
- performance graphs
- recommendation panel

---

# UX Rules

- emphasize clarity over complexity
- highlight improvement trends
- avoid overwhelming raw stats

---

# Error Handling

- fallback to cached progress
- retry sync silently

---

# Performance

- progress dashboard load <300ms
- incremental updates preferred

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader data labeling
- chart accessibility descriptions
- keyboard navigation

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Mastery calculation logic

Streak logic

Weak area detection

Widget Tests:

Progress dashboard

Heatmap UI

Streak widget

Integration Tests:

Full analytics pipeline

Sync flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating progress features:

- always compute mastery dynamically
- always aggregate cross-module data
- always support offline tracking
- never show raw unprocessed analytics directly